Author: Winnest
Title: Winnest - innovative marketplace
Body: üìå Our topic on Bitcointalk  Everyone who is familiar with the topic of cryptocurrencies knows such a forum as Bitcointalk. This is the oldest and the largest online forum dedicated to blockchain technology and cryptocurrencies. The site appeared on the Internet in 2009, when the price of Bitcoin was only one tenth of a cent. Since then, the price of the most well-known cryptocurrency has grown about 10 million times and today is $ 6289  Bitcointalk was originally created by Satoshi Nakamoto ‚Äì " father" of bitcoin, a person whose true identity is unknown (maybe he is not a person but a certain group of people communicating under one pseudonym). Incidentally, profile of Satoshi on Bitcointalk can be find even today - the last time he entered his account was on December 13, 2010 (the link on his profile https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?action=profile; u=3 )  One of Satoshi's last posts before he disappeared was about WikiLeaks in which Satoshi claimed that "WikiLeaks has squashed the hornet's nest and now the swarm is heading towards us." According to the forum itself, now there are more than 1.7 million users registered on the site who have written in general 29.5 million messages. Since the creation of Bitcointalk the content on the site has received several billion page views. On average, 403 new users are registered every day and the current ratio of men to women is 4:1.  Bitcointalk.org was built with the use of the software package with an open source software called SMF. The design and functionality of the forum have not changed since its first publication.  Nowadays, "Altcoin Ads " branch is the most popular section on Bitcointalk, and then go "Bitcoin discussions" and "Altcoin discussions" sections.
